******
[4] OIE report
Date: Wed 28 Apr 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2010; 23(17) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9185>


Foot-and-mouth disease, Japan
-----------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 28 Apr 2010 from Dr Toshiro
Kawashima, CVO, Animal Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture,
Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo, Japan

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 2
Start date: 31 Mar 2010 [see comment below]
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 20 Apr 2010
Report date: 28 Apr 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 28 Apr 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: May 2000
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Kawaminami-cho Koyu-gun, Miyazaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1019 / 5 / 0 / 1019 / 0

Outbreak 2: Kawaminami-cho Koyu-gun, Miyazaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals / Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed
/ Slaughtered
Swine / 486 / 5 / 0 / 486 / 0

Outbreak 3: Kawaminami-cho Koyu-gun, Miyazaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing
Epidemiological unit: farm (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals / Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed
/ Slaughtered
Cattle / 725 / 4 / 0 / 725 / 0

Outbreak 4: Ebino city, Miyazaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Apr 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals / Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed
/ Slaughtered
Cattle / 275 / 4 / 0 / 275 / 0

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 4
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2019 / 13 / 0 / 2019 / 0
Swine / 486 / 5 / 0 / 486 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: 4 more outbreaks were found between 24 and
28 Apr 2010.
Since the farm in Ebino was outside the movement control area
established on 20 Apr 2010, new movement restriction within 10 km [6
mi] around the farm has been implemented since 28 Apr 2010.
Concerning the outbreak in swine, a member of the staff of the
affected farm observed a breeding pig limping on 26 Apr 2010. A
veterinarian of the farm found on 27 Apr 2010 suspicious cases which
had, using the nasal speculum, vesicles and erosions as well as on
the hooves. The National Institute of Animal Health affirmed on 28
Apr 2010 by PCR that the pigs were infected with FMD virus. The farm
is located in the movement control area established on 20 Apr 2010.

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out, quarantine, movement control inside
the country, screening, disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s), vaccination prohibited, no treatment of
affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Institute of Animal Health
(national laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) /
25 Apr 2010 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) /
28 Apr 2010 / Positive
Swine / reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) /
28 Apr 2010 / Positive

