Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[While in previous reports, the Japanese authorities indicated that
the outbreak had started on 7 Apr 2010, in the current follow-up
report no. 2, the date of the start of the outbreak given is 31 Mar
2010. This may reflect findings during the epidemiological
investigations, and will explain the spread of the disease.
Identification of the virus was initially carried out on 20 Apr 2010,
followed by the application of quarantine, stamping out and animal
movement restrictions. The virus may have circulated within Japanese
territory at least 3 weeks before being identified. According to
Japan's report, so far 10 farms have been confirmed as infected. A
map is included in the follow-up 2 report, at the URL above. - Mod.AS]

[The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Japan is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/01dj>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
